**04_principles/** - System design principles
- Availability, reliability, scalability
- Consistency, fault tolerance
- Maintainability, security

**05_building-blocks/** - Core building blocks
- DNS, load balancers, databases
- Key-value stores, CDN, sequencer
- Monitoring, distributed cache
- Message queues, pub-sub
- Object storage, search
- Distributed logging, task scheduler
- Sharded counters

**06_patterns/** - Architectural patterns
- Caching, rate limiting
- Circuit breaker, CQRS
- Event-driven architecture

**07_case-studies/** - End-to-end case studies
- Each case study follows standard structure
- Diagrams co-located in `diagrams/` folder
- C4 diagrams: context, container, component

**08_failures/** - Real-world failure analysis
- Introduction to system failures
- Case studies of major outages
- Lessons learned

### References Directory

**references/** - Learning resources
- Books, papers, tools
- Not numbered (reference materials)

